# finance-bot — Laravel-style single-entry scheduler (Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh)
#
# One cron line. One. Forever. Edit `config/schedule.py` to add or remove batches.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Replace PROJECT with the absolute path to your checkout.
#   2. `crontab -e` → paste the line below.
#   3. Ensure the Mac is logged in. If the Mac is asleep at a scheduled tick the
#      tick is missed (we deliberately do NOT keep the system awake — see Q6
#      in .claude/tmp/feedback-*.md). If you need every tick to fire, run a
#      `caffeinate -i` separately or disable sleep:
#         sudo pmset -a sleep 0   # only safe when plugged in
#
# Cron table (m h dom mon dow command)
# Mac cron uses local time (ICT here).
#
PROJECT=/Users/pc7/Desktop/code/finance

# ─── The one entry ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Ticks every minute. The scheduler reads config/schedule.py and runs whichever
# tasks are due. Per-task cron expressions live in that Python file, not here.
* * * * * $PROJECT/bin/run-cron.sh schedule-run

# Anything else? Don't add it here — declare it in config/schedule.py instead.
